{"session_id":"svc-1778368340302158938","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-09T23:12:22.320264941Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"sonnet","sticky":{"key_present":true,"bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"requested_harness":"claude","resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"request_harness","requested_model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","resolved_model":"sonnet","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-46f94cee-20260509T231210-9c283665","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260509T231210-9c283665/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260509T231210-9c283665/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;`.ddx/executions/20260509T231210-9c283665/no_changes_rationale.txt` must contain one:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` reject.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260509T231210-9c283665/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260509T231210-9c283665/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-46f94cee\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003ebead/store: consolidate claim-Extra key list shared by Reopen and Unclaim\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;  Reopen and Unclaim each maintain their own inlined list of claim-related\u0026#xA;  Extra keys to clear. When a new claim metadata key is added (recently:\u0026#xA;  claimed-worktree), it must be added in both places or stale metadata\u0026#xA;  leaks into reopened/unclaimed beads. A consolidated key list would make\u0026#xA;  the cleanup atomic and audit-friendly.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;  - cli/internal/bead/store.go:823-831 Unclaim deletes claimed-at,\u0026#xA;    claimed-pid, claimed-machine, claimed-session, claimed-worktree,\u0026#xA;    plus assignee, plus other inline keys.\u0026#xA;  - cli/internal/bead/store.go:1306-1317 Reopen deletes the same set plus\u0026#xA;    execute-loop-heartbeat-at and walks an additional inline-event cleanup\u0026#xA;    block at lines 1329-1334.\u0026#xA;  - cli/internal/bead/reconcile.go:9-26 already declares some Extra-key\u0026#xA;    constants (ExtraExecutionEligible, ExtraExecutionReason, etc.) but\u0026#xA;    not the claim metadata set.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;  - Add a single canonical declaration of claim-metadata Extra keys in\u0026#xA;    cli/internal/bead/lifecycle.go (alongside the lifecycle constants) or\u0026#xA;    cli/internal/bead/types.go (alongside CanonicalStatuses):\u0026#xA;        var ClaimMetadataExtraKeys = []string{\u0026#xA;            \u0026#34;claimed-at\u0026#34;,\u0026#xA;            \u0026#34;claimed-pid\u0026#34;,\u0026#xA;            \u0026#34;claimed-machine\u0026#34;,\u0026#xA;            \u0026#34;claimed-session\u0026#34;,\u0026#xA;            \u0026#34;claimed-worktree\u0026#34;,\u0026#xA;        }\u0026#xA;    plus separate constants for ClaimAssigneeExtraKey (\u0026#34;assignee\u0026#34;) and\u0026#xA;    ClaimHeartbeatExtraKey (\u0026#34;execute-loop-heartbeat-at\u0026#34;) if they need\u0026#xA;    distinct cleanup rules.\u0026#xA;  - Refactor Unclaim (store.go:823-831) to iterate ClaimMetadataExtraKeys\u0026#xA;    instead of inlining delete calls. Preserve the order of operations:\u0026#xA;    clear assignee, clear claim metadata, then clear heartbeat.\u0026#xA;  - Refactor Reopen (store.go:1306-1317) similarly, plus preserve the\u0026#xA;    inline-event cleanup at 1329-1334 unchanged (different concern).\u0026#xA;  - Add a unit test TestClaimMetadataKeys_SharedByReopenAndUnclaim in\u0026#xA;    cli/internal/bead/store_test.go that:\u0026#xA;      a. Claims a bead, populates every key in ClaimMetadataExtraKeys plus\u0026#xA;         assignee and execute-loop-heartbeat-at.\u0026#xA;      b. Calls Unclaim; asserts every key in ClaimMetadataExtraKeys is\u0026#xA;         absent from b.Extra.\u0026#xA;      c. Re-claims, then calls Reopen; asserts the same.\u0026#xA;      d. Adds a deliberately new key to b.Extra not in\u0026#xA;         ClaimMetadataExtraKeys (e.g. \u0026#34;claim-test-extra\u0026#34;); asserts it\u0026#xA;         survives both Unclaim and Reopen (proving the cleanup is bounded\u0026#xA;         by the canonical list).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;  - Changing the actual fields the system writes during claim acquisition.\u0026#xA;  - Renaming or moving the Extra keys; their string values are unchanged.\u0026#xA;  - Touching the inline-event cleanup at store.go:1329-1334 (separate\u0026#xA;    concern: events, not claim metadata).\u0026#xA;  - Migrating existing beads with stale metadata; that is a separate\u0026#xA;    reconcile path.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;INTERSECTIONS\u0026#xA;  - ddx-ca1c66ee (epic parent).\u0026#xA;  - No deps on B1/B2/B3/B4/B5; can run in parallel.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. ClaimMetadataExtraKeys (or equivalent canonical list) is declared in cli/internal/bead/lifecycle.go or cli/internal/bead/types.go with at minimum the keys claimed-at, claimed-pid, claimed-machine, claimed-session, claimed-worktree.\u0026#xA;2. cli/internal/bead/store.go Unclaim (around line 823-831) iterates the canonical list instead of inlining individual delete calls per key.\u0026#xA;3. cli/internal/bead/store.go Reopen (around line 1306-1317) iterates the canonical list instead of inlining individual delete calls per key.\u0026#xA;4. TestClaimMetadataKeys_SharedByReopenAndUnclaim in cli/internal/bead/store_test.go asserts the four properties in PROPOSED FIX (Unclaim clears all listed keys, Reopen clears all listed keys, an unrelated Extra key survives, the canonical list is the bound).\u0026#xA;5. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/bead/... ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... green.\u0026#xA;6. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:6, area:bead, area:lifecycle, kind:refactor, spec:TD-031\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-ca1c66ee\" spec-id=\"TD-031\" base-rev=\"882f68b4dd2e4076826d544d0da3327912aea53a\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260509T231210-9c283665\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"TD-031\" path=\"docs/helix/02-design/technical-designs/TD-031-bead-state-machine.md\"\u003eTechnical Design: Bead State Machine and Naming-Role Decisions\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","attempt_id":"20260509T231210-9c283665","base_rev":"882f68b4dd2e4076826d544d0da3327912aea53a","bead_id":"ddx-46f94cee","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260509T231210-9c283665","correlation_id":"ddx-46f94cee:20260509T231210-9c283665","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260509T231210-9c283665/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"bfe6c7ec0e2813af8b74565057267cda2c3834f1b122395f438cee083737883c","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-034c9e2a","worker_id":""}}}
